  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to compare 12-month results of two single initial
      treatments—photodynamic therapy with verteporfin alone and this therapy combined with
      intravitreal bevacizumab—for neovascular age-related macular degeneration, not including
      patients with polypoidal choroidal vasculopathy who were presumed to have age-related macular
      degeneration.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
